<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#D0BC90">Originally posted by LintMan on 11-18-2002 11:07 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Unfortunately, crossbows seem all-around inferior to regular bows.  I've yet (at level 38!) to find a crossbow with greater than 70 damage or so, compared to the 193 damage hunter's bow I've found.  If the bow skills don't apply to crossbows (as mentioned here - I haven't verified this myself, and it seems quite unfair), I don't see any benefit at all in using a crossbow.  Could there be some other aspect to crossbows that makes them worth using?  One handed, or much faster firing rate or something?  I don't know, but it seems unlikely it would make up for not having any elemental damage skills available.

I'm not so sure of some of the facts in the other ranger thread linked here.  Someone states there that Poison/Spirit/Elemental damage don't do anything.  I've found they all work fine.  I suspect that the poster thought these skills are passive like the melee versions, but they are not, so you need to right-click to use them, and I believe the damage they list is total damage, not a damage bonus.  

That said, I think bows combined with the ranger path elemental skills work great and are very powerful, especially elemental arrow and exploding arrow.  I cleared the Orc camp with one point in Elemental arrow, one in 
true shot, and one in bow, using an average long bow.  Prior to that, I struggled badly against the orcs using my heavily beefed-up melee skills (many sword points, plus some several poison/stun points).  Elemental arrow just mowed 'em down.

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
